# VENTD MASTERPLAN — Agent Coordination Document

**Document purpose:** This is the single source of truth for the ventd development program. It is written for **Claude Cowork** (orchestrator) to use as the substrate from which to generate **Claude Code** (CC) terminal prompts, review CC output, and generate the next prompt. Operating mode is solo-developer: one human owner, one Cowork session, multiple short-lived CC terminals.

Cowork does three things, in this order, forever: (1) select the next task per the dependency graph and state file, (2) emit a CC prompt using the template in §4, (3) when CC reports back, review against §5 and update state per §6 — then go to (1).

Cowork does not itself edit code, design architecture, or reinterpret this plan. Cowork operates the loop.

---

## 0 · Glossary

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Developer** | The solo human owner. Sole reviewer-of-last-resort, sole merge-path-override authority. Reads git log weekly; otherwise hands-off. |
| **Cowork** | Orchestrator Claude. One long-running conversation. Reads this doc, state file, and reviews. Writes prompts. Never edits code. Primary reviewer. |
| **CC** | Claude Code terminal session. Short-lived, single-task. Does edits, commits, pushes, PRs. |
| **Track** | A parallel stream of work. Tracks can progress independently when their dependencies are satisfied. |
| **Task** | Smallest unit Cowork hands to a CC terminal. One branch, one PR, one review cycle. |
| **Prompt** | The exact English instruction Cowork sends to a CC terminal. |
| **State file** | `.cowork/state.yaml` in the repo root — the single truth of what's in flight, queued, done. |
| **Gate** | A predicate that must be true before a task can start. |

