## 4 · CC prompt template

```
You are Claude Code, working on the ventd repository.

## Task
ID: {task_id}
Track: {track_id}
Goal: {one-sentence goal}

## Context you should read first
{list of files to Read; keep under 15 unless the task genuinely needs more}

## What to do
{numbered list of concrete steps. Each step actionable by a single tool call
 or a small group of them.}

## Definition of done
{bullet list of acceptance criteria, each one independently verifiable}

## Out of scope for this task
{list anything an eager CC might wander into. ALWAYS include: "Adding,
modifying, or removing tests. A parallel stream owns the test suite."}

## Branch and PR
- Work on branch: {branch_name}
- Commit style: conventional commits
- Open a draft PR on completion with title: "{pr_title}"
- PR description must include: the goal verbatim, bulleted files-touched list,
  "How I verified" section, link back to task ID: {task_id}

## Constraints
- Do not touch files outside this list unless necessary: {allowlist}
- Do not add new direct dependencies without explicit permission
- Keep the main binary CGO_ENABLED=0 compatible
- Preserve all existing safety guarantees (watchdog restore, PWM clamping)
- If blocked, push WIP, open draft PR with "[BLOCKED]" prefix, write a
  "Blocker" section in the description.

## Reporting
On completion:
- STATUS: done | partial | blocked
- PR: <url>
- SUMMARY: <= 200 words
- CONCERNS: second-guessing you had while working
- FOLLOWUPS: work you noticed that isn't in scope
```

Cowork rules when filling the template:
1. Never include the word "test" in "What to do".
2. Keep the file read-list short.
3. Acceptance criteria must be verifiable without live hardware.
4. "Out of scope" always includes tests, unrelated refactors, dependency bumps, and formatting changes in files not otherwise touched.

