## 5 · Review checklist

Cowork is the reviewer. Any ambiguous row is `revise`, not a judgement call.

| Row | Check |
|---|---|
| R1 | PR opened as draft with the task ID in the description |
| R2 | Branch name matches the assigned name |
| R3 | Commits follow conventional-commits format |
| R4 | Files touched subset of allowlist OR deviation justified in PR |
| R5 | No test files touched, or exactly the minimum noted with TEST-TOUCHED |
| R6 | CI is green OR failures are env flakes explicitly called out |
| R7 | Every acceptance criterion visibly satisfied in the diff |
| R8 | No new direct dependencies OR addition explicitly permitted |
| R9 | Safety guarantees preserved: watchdog.Restore paths, PWM clamping, pwm_enable save/restore unchanged unless task targets them |
| R10 | No secrets, credentials, or real hardware fingerprints committed |
| R11 | CHANGELOG.md updated under "## Unreleased" with one-line entry |
| R12 | Public API not changed unless task targets it |
| R13 | PR does not touch more than one track's files |
| R14 | go vet, golangci-lint, gofmt all clean |
| R15 | Binary size delta ≤ +100 KB outside Phase 6 unless SIZE-JUSTIFIED |
| R16 | No panic/log.Fatal/os.Exit added outside cmd main.go paths |
| R17 | Every new goroutine has clear lifecycle (ctx or stop channel) |
| R18 | Every file reader/writer deferred Close or justified |

