## 9 · Public roadmap (source for P0-02)

> **ventd 1.0 arc.** Cross-platform first: the single fan-control daemon for Linux, Windows, macOS, BSD. Every fan type: hwmon, GPU, IPMI, USB AIOs, laptop EC, ARM SBC PWM. Learning control: a per-machine thermal model quietens fans by predicting load. Curated profiles: first boot is zero-touch on any hardware already seen. Acoustic health: detect bearing failures from sound alone. One static binary, zero capabilities, 2-second guaranteed safe exit.

---

## 10 · Decision heuristics

1. Prefer tasks on tracks with no in-flight work (fan out).
2. Prefer tasks whose merge unblocks most descendants (critical path).
3. Prefer smaller allowlists first when (1)+(2) tie.
4. Never assign two in-flight tasks sharing an allowlist file.
5. Never advance a phase while Phase-N task is in_flight or review; advancement is a manual gate the developer flips after §15 checkpoint.

---

## 11 · Review artifact format

`.cowork/reviews/<review-id>.md`:
```
# Review <review-id>
Task: <task-id>
PR: <url>
Verdict: accept | revise | reject
Checklist:
  R1: ✅ / ❌ <note>
  R2: ...
Notes:
  <free text>
```

---

## 12 · Escalation

Append to `.cowork/ESCALATIONS.md` on cowork/state. Stop relevant track (or loop).

Triggers: 3 same-row revise failures; infra CI failures; unauthorised dep bumps; schema-breaking API/config; security-sensitive paths beyond task scope; TEST-TOUCHED without note; phase's first PR; LICENSE/SECURITY.md/CODEOWNERS/deploy sandbox touches.

Entry:
```
## <ISO-8601> <subject>
Task: <task-id or —>
PR: <url or —>
Reason: <one paragraph>
Recommended action: <RESUME | DROP | REWRITE | developer-choice>
```

Developer signals: `RESUME <task-id>` · `DROP <task-id>` · `REWRITE <task-id> <new-allowlist>`.

